## Git Commands — Full Reference

### 🔧 Setup & Config
| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `git --version` | Check Git is installed |
| `git config --global user.name "Your Name"` | Set your name (shows in commits) |
| `git config --global user.email "you@email.com"` | Set your email |
| `git config --list` | View all your config settings |

---

### 📁 Starting a Project
| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `git init` | Turn any folder into a Git repo |
| `git clone <url>` | Download a repo from GitHub to your machine |
| `git clone <url> myfolder` | Clone into a specific folder name |

---

### 👀 Checking Status
| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `git status` | See what's changed / staged / untracked |
| `git diff` | See exact line changes (not yet staged) |
| `git diff --staged` | See changes already staged (ready to commit) |
| `git log` | Full commit history |
| `git log --oneline` | Short one-line history (cleaner) |
| `git log --oneline --graph` | Visual branch tree |
| `git show <commit-id>` | See what changed in a specific commit |

---

### ➕ Staging & Committing
| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `git add filename.py` | Stage one specific file |
| `git add .` | Stage ALL changed files |
| `git add -p` | Stage changes piece by piece (interactive) |
| `git commit -m "Your message"` | Save a snapshot with a message |
| `git commit -am "message"` | Stage + commit tracked files in one step |
| `git commit --amend -m "new msg"` | Fix the last commit message |

---

### 🌿 Branching
| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `git branch` | List all local branches |
| `git branch -a` | List all branches (local + remote) |
| `git branch feature-name` | Create a new branch |
| `git checkout feature-name` | Switch to a branch |
| `git checkout -b feature-name` | Create AND switch in one command ← use this |
| `git branch -d feature-name` | Delete a branch (safe — merged only) |
| `git branch -D feature-name` | Force delete a branch |
| `git switch feature-name` | Modern way to switch branches |
| `git switch -c feature-name` | Modern way to create + switch |

---

### 🔀 Merging & Rebasing
| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `git merge feature-name` | Merge a branch into your current branch |
| `git merge --abort` | Cancel a merge if conflicts are messy |
| `git rebase main` | Replay your branch commits on top of main |
| `git rebase --abort` | Cancel a rebase |

---

### ☁️ Remote (GitHub)
| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `git remote -v` | See your connected remote URLs |
| `git remote add origin <url>` | Link your local repo to GitHub |
| `git push origin main` | Upload main branch to GitHub |
| `git push -u origin main` | Upload + set upstream (do once, then just `git push`) |
| `git push origin feature-name` | Push a specific branch |
| `git push --force` | Force push (dangerous — overwrites remote) |
| `git pull` | Download + merge latest from GitHub |
| `git pull origin main` | Pull specifically from main |
| `git fetch` | Download changes but DON'T merge yet |

---

### ↩️ Undoing Mistakes
| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `git restore filename.py` | Discard unsaved changes to a file |
| `git restore --staged filename.py` | Unstage a file (keep changes) |
| `git revert <commit-id>` | Undo a commit safely (creates new commit) |
| `git reset --soft HEAD~1` | Undo last commit, keep changes staged |
| `git reset --mixed HEAD~1` | Undo last commit, keep changes unstaged |
| `git reset --hard HEAD~1` | Undo last commit + DELETE all changes ⚠️ |
| `git clean -fd` | Delete all untracked files & folders ⚠️ |

---

### 📦 Stash (Temporary Save)
| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `git stash` | Temporarily save dirty work (not committed) |
| `git stash list` | See all stashed saves |
| `git stash pop` | Bring back your stash + remove it from list |
| `git stash apply` | Bring back stash but KEEP it in list |
| `git stash drop` | Delete a stash permanently |

---

### 🏷️ Tags
| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `git tag v1.0` | Mark current commit as v1.0 |
| `git tag` | List all tags |
| `git push origin v1.0` | Push a tag to GitHub |
| `git push origin --tags` | Push all tags to GitHub |

---

## GitHub-Specific Actions (done on the website or via `gh` CLI)

| Action | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Fork** | Copy someone else's repo to your account |
| **Pull Request (PR)** | Request to merge your branch into main |
| **Issues** | Report a bug or request a feature |
| **Star** | Bookmark a useful repo |
| **Watch** | Get notified of repo activity |
| **GitHub Actions** | Auto-run tests/deploy on every push (CI/CD) |
| **Secrets** | Store API keys safely (not in code) |
| **GitHub Pages** | Publish a website from your repo |

---

## The 6 Commands You'll Use Every Single Day

```bash
git status           # always start here
git add .            # stage everything
git commit -m "..."  # save snapshot
git push             # upload to GitHub
git pull             # get latest from GitHub
git checkout -b ...  # start new branch for new work
```

